ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='I can see from the log that after login, the app is trying to tap `ta
b_messages` but it\'s not found. This means the UI after login doesn\'t have a `
tab_messages` element with that ID. Similarly, `mode_tab_nearby` is not found in
the swipe_recommendations flow.\n\nI need to look at the screenshots to understa
nd what the actual UI looks like after login. Let me read the screenshots for th
e failed flows.\n\nAlso, for `login` flow - it passed but with a warning: `tab_h
ome` was optional and not found. So the app after login doesn\'t have `tab_home`
either! It seems like after login, the user is on the "完善资料" (profile setup)
page, not the home page.\n\nWait, looking at `login` flow result:\n- `assertNotV
isible: "手机号一键登录"` - passed\n- `assertVisible: text: "完善资料" optional:
true` - passed\n- `assertVisible: id: "tab_home" optional: true` - WARNED (not f
ound)\n\nSo after login with clear state, the user is on the profile setup page,
not the home page. This makes sense if the test user is a new user.\n\nBut then 
`setup` flow passed - it runs login, then profile setup actions, and then option
ally asserts `tab_home`. But wait, `setup` passed! So after profile setup, the u
ser DOES get to a page... but `tab_home` might still not be there, or it might b
e optional and passed.\n\nWait, the `setup` flow doesn\'t assert `tab_home` dire
ctly - it only runs `profile-setup-actions.yaml` when "完善资料" is visible, and
then at the end it doesn\'t assert anything about the home page. Actually let me
re-read `setup.yaml`:\n\n```yaml\n- assertNotVisible: "手机号一键登录"\n- runFlo
w:\n    when:\n      visible: "完善资料"\n    file: includes/profile-setup-actio
ns.yaml\n- assertVisible:\n    id: "tab_home"\n    optional: true\n```\n\nHmm, `
setup.yaml` does assert `tab_home` optionally at the end. Since it\'s optional, 
it warns but passes.\n\nSo the main issues are:\n1. After login/setup, the app d
oesn\'t have `tab_home`, `tab_messages`, `mode_tab_nearby` elements visible\n2. 
This could mean:\n   a. The UI elements have different IDs\n   b. The app is on 
a different page than expected\n   c. The app crashed or shows an error\n\nLet m
e look at the screenshots.',
